comment:
So there was a few things that I specifically noticed in AH's sister's testimony today:

1: Whitney's states "... she does not remember Heard talking about it yesterday..." (Are AH even allowed to talk with her sister regarding the case while AH is still testifying? If I remember correctly, JD was not allowed to, and the way Whitney phrases it, it sounds like they indeed have talked about the case, just not about the picture)

2: Regarding the painting. AH testified yesterday (i believe) that the painting - incident was in fact 2 different paintings. BUT Whitney, accidently says it was 1 painting (Changing the name to Van Pee, AND being burned on the back) before she suddenly changes it to, "it was two different paintings" later in her testimony.

3: Whitney have had 3 weeks to amend her statement regarding the "right" dates i March, but chose to do it today? Doesn't seem credible. The moment she realized the date was wrong, she should have amended it, right?

4: How could Whitney AND Amber forget about the cast that Johnny had on? And I do not think it is possible to grab Ambers hair with one hand, and hit Amber with the other, when his hand was in a cast. the lawyer should have asked which hand Johnny used to punch Amber.

5: (Kind of just a side note): Whitney testifies that there was indeed a red bull in the incident, where Amber stated, that she didn't even drink red bull, and made i sound like it wasn't even there, but her sister kind of ruined that illusion. Besides... you don't have to be the one drinking it, to throw it. AND, why have AH's side not asked for the nurses testimony to back AH's story regarding that night, since Whitney claims the red bull hit the nurse? AND one more thing regarding that incident. Why did Whitney not do anything and just watched JD hit Amber mulitple times in the face? JD had a cast on, so she should have been able to intervene, but she didn't?

6: Did Whitney just add a detail to the bed framing thingy? Not even Amber mentions that, there was blood and hair on the bed frame that had been ruined. AND IF that was the case... why did Amber or Whitney not take a picture of THAT? but only taking a picture of it being ruined? (You do mention this in the video)

7: Its propably a very touchy subject, but I am gonna state it anyway. Whitney says, it was her who vomited in the parking lot, due to pregnancy, at AH's 30th birthday. And this is where it gets touchy... did she lose the child? The incident was supposed to have taken place in 2016? (correct me if I am wrong with the year of the incident) but if you look at Whitney's insta, you will notice that she only mentions a pregnancy i 2018.(She has only 1 child that she herself gave birth too ((she is also a stepmother))), so one can only conclude, 1 out of 2 things. 1: She lost the child i 2016 or  2: She was never pregnant to begin with, but said so to help AH with her narrative. I think it is worth for JD's lawyers to look into, or hear from JD himself wether that statement is true or not. 

8: (Another side note, that you also mention): Whitney kind of destroyed the Sun's and Amber's argument regarding the staged picture... Omg was I laughing hard when I read that... 

I just thought it was a bit weird. Or maybe bc AH has spouted so many lies, I will automaticly assume  everything from AH's side is a lie,  even when/if there is a spec of truth, I have difficulty believing it, simply bc I feel they could/would lie about anything/everything if they were to profit from it. (or to save their own skin). 

Any thoughts on this?
And thx for your update <3
